        <item>
          <title>AMD Radeon Drivers Reveal FSR 4 DLL File: Implications for RDNA 3 and Handheld Gaming PCs</title>
          <description><![CDATA[Unofficial AMD Radeon drivers have revealed the existence of an FSR 4 DLL file, suggesting that RDNA 4 GPUs will be required to access this new upscaling method. This could have significant implications for handheld gaming PCs, particularly those using Ryzen Z2 Extreme APUs with built-in RDNA 3.5 architecture.]]></description>
